final_robot_safe_realtime.py
Realtime Whisper (utterance-level) + (Rule-based move priority) + MiniLM intent routing + UR RTDE control
+ CSV metrics logging

+ Real robot safety enhancements:
  - Movement disabled until armed via START
  - STOP/DISARM has highest priority override
  - Single movement distance clamp (default/max step)
  - XYZ workspace boundary clamp
  - RULE_MOVE executes only after a second confirmation ("yes/no") using pending_move
  - (Optional) Port check: 29999 (dashboard), 30004 (RTDE)
  - Briefing (TTS) integration + ASR muted while TTS is speaking (prevents TTS→mic feedback loop)
  - Audio queue cleared after each utterance is processed
  - Audio queue input blocked during ASR transcription

Usage:
  python final_robot_safe_realtime.py --host 192.168.10.11 --device 1
  python final_robot_safe_realtime.py --host 192.168.10.11 --dry-run
  python final_robot_safe_realtime.py --list-devices
